post_text:
In an effort to prevent the spread of the COVID-19 virus within our staff and student body we are asking all parents/guardians, of students who will be in attendance on-site, and all employees to notify our designated Point of Contact immediately when the following occurs:

‚Ä¢ Someone in the household has tested positive for COVID 19.
‚Ä¢ Someone in the household has been identified as a Close Contact to a positive case of COVID 19 and is requiring quarantine and/or recommended to be tested for COVID 19.
‚Ä¢ Student attending on-site and employees who are being tested for COVID-19. If symptomatic, student/staff should remain in quarantine pending results of their COVID 19 test.

Please call Joycelyn Brandon at (870) 295-1022 or email information to Joycelyn.brandon@lcsdtrojans.net. Thank you in advance for your cooperation. Together we can help keep our Lee County School District family safe, healthy, and ready to learn during this unique time.

post_text:
Trojans Family,

The AMI paper packet process is now more convenient! Located outside of Anna Strong Learning Academy gymnasium, 12 newspaper bins have been filled with your scholars' AMI paper packets. Each bin has a poster indicating the grade level and content area.

Two return bins are located under the awning across from the gymnasium doors. One return bin is for LHS scholars. The other return bin is for ASLA and Whitten PreK scholars. When returning AMI packets, please return the packet in the provided manilla envelope and note your scholar's name.

Scholars are permitted to move from AMI paper packets to completing AMI instruction via the online portals. District electronic devices are still available for check out Monday - Friday from 11:00 a.m.- 1:00 p.m. Thank you for your partnership and commitment to the BEST scholars in the land! #WeAreTrojans

Greetings Trojans Family. Today, Governor Hutchinson announced that all Arkansas public schools will be closed for the remainder of the 2019-2020 school year. However, online (AMI) instruction will continue.

Please see the info graphic below for additional details regarding AMI instruction.

We are living in a season of change, but we can assure you that we will continue to provide our scholars with the best education, although the methods are different. Thank you for your partnership and continued support of our LCSD scholars.

#WeAreTrojans

The Lee County School District will be closed Monday, March 16, 2020. By order of Gov. Hutchinson ALL Arkansas schools will be closed Tuesday, March 17, 2020 through Sunday, March 29, 2020 due to the concerns surrounding the COVID-19 (coronavirus) outbreak. Schools will reopen on Monday, March 30, 2020 unless otherwise ordered by Gov. Hutchinson.

As of today there are no presumed positive cases of COVID-19 in the Lee County area. The district will continue to provide updates as they occur.

The District will also provide meals the week of March 16, 2020 from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. at the Anna Strong Learning Academy. AMI packets K-12 will also be available on sites.

March 5th and 6th the Lee County School District will take AMI (Alternative Method of Instruction) days due to sickness (flu/strep) of students and staff. The health and safety of our students and staff will always be our number one priority. We do understand the stress this puts on families, students, and staff. We hope that the upcoming four days (including the weekend) will help combat the spread of illness and give students and staff time to get well and return healthy on March 9th. During this time we will perform a deep cleaning of our facilities and transportation fleet to ensure a healthy environment conducive for student learning.

While transportation services for tomorrow night's ball game will not be made available due to cleaning, we do hope to see you in attendance to support our Mighty Trojans as they compete in the 2nd round of state tournament play. üñ§üíõ

Thank you for understanding and support.
#WeAreTrojans

#TrojanStrongTrojanTrue
shared_text:
Marianna Area Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc.
December 16, 2019 at 11:05 PM ¬∑

Marianna Area Alumnae Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority Inc. joined in with the community tonight at Lee High School home game to bring awareness of AIDS and HIV. The community was handed red ribbons at the entrance and the LHS Senior Boys wore red socks. At halftime, the audience stood with MAAC for a moment of silence for those individuals who are still fighting and for those who lost their lives with AIDS. Special thanks to the Athletic Director Coach DJ Vincent and Principal Rafeal Smith for the warm welcome. Congratulations! Trojans on their win tonight.

Anna Strong Learning Academy
Staff Member of the Week | Kehila Gardner

Ms. Gardner was selected as bi-weekly staff of the week because she consistently adheres to District Priority number 4: High Expectations.

This is evident in how she speaks positively about her scholars to other staff and provides consistent scholar feedback. Said feedback improves academic performance while increasing scholar confidence.

Ms. Gardner also exhibits alignment with District Priority number 2: Strong Instruction. Scholars are given the opportunity to voice their opinions and showcase learning in a validating atmosphere in a variety of ways.
Ms. Gardner, thank you for all you do to exemplify what it means to be an ASLA Staff member.
